---

## Stack: Java 25 + Quarkus 3.33 LTS + Gradle 9.4

This project was scaffolded with the **java-quarkus** keel profile.

### Layout

```
domain/
  kernel/        # mediator + result + handler interfaces; depends on nothing
  contract/      # commands, queries, errors, port interfaces; depends on kernel
  core/          # handlers + mediator implementation; depends on kernel + contract
application/
  rest/
    contract/    # OpenAPI spec + transport DTOs; depends on domain/contract
    executable/  # Quarkus runnable; composition root, JAX-RS resources, mediator wiring
infrastructure/
  <port>/<impl>/ # real adapters; never depended on by domain
  <port>/fake/   # canonical fake; used by tests
build-logic/     # Gradle convention plugins (java/quality/test conventions)
gradle/
  libs.versions.toml  # version catalog — pinned, refresh quarterly
iac/             # OpenTofu modules + bootstrap scripts
.github/         # CI / CD workflows
```

### Default endpoints (dev mode)

| URL                                  | What                |
| ------------------------------------ | ------------------- |
| `http://localhost:8080/`             | the service         |
| `http://localhost:8080/q/dev`        | Quarkus Dev UI      |
| `http://localhost:8080/q/swagger-ui` | Swagger UI          |
| `http://localhost:8080/q/openapi`    | live OpenAPI 3.1    |
| `http://localhost:8080/q/health`     | liveness/readiness  |

### Skills available in this profile

- **`build`** — `./gradlew build`, native packaging, what `check` wraps.
- **`test`** — JUnit 5, RestAssured, ArchUnit, Pitest mutation runs.
- **`run`** — Quarkus dev mode, hot reload, debugger attach.
- **`format`** — `./gradlew spotlessApply` (Google Java Format).
- **`troubleshoot`** — port conflicts, toolchain issues, native-image,
  ArchUnit failures, hot-reload edge cases.

Each skill is a runbook; consult before guessing.

### Quick command reference

| Goal                          | Command                                            |
| ----------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| run locally with hot reload   | `./gradlew quarkusDev`                             |
| full build + tests + checks   | `./gradlew build`                                  |
| run all tests                 | `./gradlew test`                                   |
| run one test                  | `./gradlew test --tests com.example.Foo`           |
| auto-format                   | `./gradlew spotlessApply`                          |
| mutation tests                | `./gradlew pitest`                                 |
| native build (GraalVM CE 25)  | `./gradlew build -Dquarkus.package.type=native`    |
| attach debugger               | `./gradlew quarkusDev -Ddebug=5005 -Dsuspend=true` |

### Conventions reminders specific to this stack

- **Composition root:** `application/rest/executable` is the only
  module allowed to wire concrete adapters and handlers. Keep the
  JAX-RS layer (`application/rest/contract`) free of business logic
  — it dispatches via the mediator and translates `Result` ↔ HTTP.
- **OpenAPI:** the spec file under
  `application/rest/contract/src/main/resources/openapi/` is the
  contract; the runtime spec at `/q/openapi` is generated from
  annotations. Keep both in sync.
- **Port fakes:** every secondary port ships an
  `infrastructure/<port>/fake` module — that's the canonical reference
  implementation tests depend on. Real adapters never substitute for
  fakes in tests.
- **Toolchain:** Java 25 is pinned in `build-logic`. Don't downgrade
  to chase a dependency — bump the dependency.
